727971f-a.title: Queens: Seaside Avenue - Beach Channel Drive
727971f-a.text:
Seaside Avenue, east side, between Beach Channel Drive
and the Long -sland Railroad tracks, Far Rockaway, showing
the Seaside Hotel of 1891, remodelled. One Wainright built
the original Seaside House, a three-story peak-roofed house,
in 1874. Sanford Murray was manager in the 70's; Harper
Stumpf the proprietor in 1881; and O.D. Potter in 1901. It
was known as the Seaside in 1891. Mr. Armbruster is authority
for the above data.
View 1: Eugene L. Armbruster Collection  1924
MAY BE REPRODUCED
View 2: G. L. Balgue
CREDIT LINE IMPERATIVE  1928
